TITANIUM-4: Low-Latency Intrusion Detection via Early Benign Isolation and Hierarchical Attack Forensics
     
Authors: Muhammad Younas, Sadeeda*, Hoor ul Ain, Huzaifa Shahzad, Ihsan Ul Haq, Muhammad Farooq
Affiliation: Department of Electrical Engineering, University of Engineering and Technology, Peshawar, Pakistan
Dataset: CSE-CIC-IDS2018
________________________________________
Abstract
TITANIUM-4 is a four-layer intrusion detection pipeline designed for inline deployment on hardware switches with 10-15 ms timing constraints. The system employs three-tier routing: a calibrated LightGBM binary gatekeeper (Layer 2) isolates benign traffic early (82.5% of flows exit after Layer 2), an eight-class multiclass forensics classifier (Layer 3) labels attack families, and an OC-SVM sentinel (Layer 4) detects zero-day threats without attack labels. End-to-end latency is 7.91 ms (p50), meeting hardware-switch budgets. Live evaluation on 11,138 DoS Hulk flows quantifies significant domain shift and demonstrates recovery via adaptive thresholding.
________________________________________
Architecture
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                        TITANIUM-4 Pipeline                       │
├──────────┬──────────┬──────────────┬────────────────────────────┤
│ Layer 1  │ Layer 2  │ Layer 3      │ Layer 4                    │
│ Ingestion│ Gatekeeper│ Forensics   │ Sentinel                   │
├──────────┼──────────┼──────────────┼────────────────────────────┤
│ Robust   │ LightGBM │ LightGBM     │ OC-SVM (RBF)               │
│ Scaler   │ Binary   │ 8-class      │ nu=0.01, gamma=scale       │
│ 4.74 ms  │ 1.10 ms  │ 1.43 ms      │ 0.64 ms                    │
│          │ F1=0.9999│ macro-F1=    │ AUC=0.8205                 │
│          │ AUC=0.9999│ 0.9867      │ DR=45.06% @ 5% FPR         │
└──────────┴──────────┴──────────────┴────────────────────────────┘
     │            │              │                  │
     └────────────┴──────────────┴──────────────────┘
                    7.91 ms end-to-end
Routing Logic
Path	Condition	Flows	Latency
Benign	L2 score < tau_B	82.5%	L1 + L2 + L4 = 4.74 ms
Known Attack	L2 score >= tau_B AND L3 confidence >= tau_M	17.5%	L1 + L2 + L3 = 3.17 ms
Uncertain	L2 score >= tau_B AND L3 confidence < tau_M	<0.1%	L1 + L2 + L4 = 4.74 ms
________________________________________
Key Results
Benchmark (CSE-CIC-IDS2018, 1,176,820 flows)
Component	Metric	Value
L2 Gatekeeper	AUC	0.99997
	F1	0.99987
	FPR	0.00000
L3 Forensics	Macro-F1 (test)	0.9867
	Macro-F1 (validation)	0.9551
	tau_M (confidence threshold)	0.999999
L4 Sentinel	AUC	0.8205
	Detection Rate (5% FPR)	45.06%
	tau_U (95th percentile)	1.385 x 10^-6
Live Test (DoS Hulk, 11,138 flows)
Metric	Value
Total flows	11,138
Attack flows	5,810 (52.2%)
Benign-routed flows	5,328 (47.8%)
L2 detection rate	52.2%
tau_B’ (adapted)	0.0001
tau_U’ (adapted)	3000
Sentinel recovery	516 flows (9.7%)
Combined detection	56.9%
Max live probability	0.0138 (vs. benchmark tau_B = 1.0)
________________________________________
Quick Start
Requirements
Python >= 3.9
RAM >= 16 GB
Installation
git clone https://github.com/EngrMuhammadYounas/TITANIUM-4-IDS.git
cd TITANIUM-4-IDS
pip install -r requirements.txt
Download CSE-CIC-IDS2018
# Place CSV files in data/cse-cic-ids2018/
# Dataset: https://www.unb.ca/cic/datasets/ids-2018.html
Run Inference
# Benchmark evaluation
python src/IDSmodel.py --mode benchmark --input data/cse-cic-ids2018/ --models models/

# Live traffic evaluation (PCAP)
python src/livetest.py --pcap capture.pcap --models models/ --output results/live/
